- Security groups -> ports, protocols, source and destination
- Network access control list (NACL) specify allow/deny rules for traffic in and out of a subnet.
- VPC can be peered to allow traffic between VPCs including diff regions and AWS accounts - like being on same network
- VPC can be access via a virtual private network
- Route table to control traffic in and out of subnet
- Provide access to external internet with an internet gateway [Internet gateway associated with VPC]
- Use NAT gateway to provide external internet access for private subnets
- VPC flow logs provide information about network connections

